SECTION 5 — AUDIENCE INTELLIGENCE
who_they_are:

Club fans — predominantly women 16–35 — who follow a specific team, not just the sport generally. They watch matches, own kit, and want their personal style to reflect club loyalty without looking like they've raided a merchandise stall. Mix of Premier League fans (Arsenal, Chelsea, Tottenham, Man United), La Liga fans (Real Madrid, Barcelona), Bundesliga fans (Dortmund), and MLS fans (Inter Miami, Seattle Sounders). Many are searching specifically around World Cup 2026 season, which has reignited club-pride energy.
what_they_want_from_this_post:

Design ideas that feel fashion-forward, not costume-y. They want to know exactly what to show their nail tech or how to DIY a look that is recognisably their club without spelling it out in giant letters. Club colour palette translation into a real wearable manicure is the core need.
what_frustrates_them:

Content that just says "use team colours" — no specificity
Real Madrid tutorials that are beautiful but only serve Madrid fans
Generic soccer nail content that ignores club identity entirely
No guidance on making club nails wearable for daily life, not just match days

